# Pakistan LegalAI — Cursor Rules
# Author: Antigravity | Version: 5.0.0

You are assisting with the **Pakistan LegalAI** project — an AI-powered legal assistance platform for Pakistani citizens. Follow these conventions precisely when writing, debugging, or modifying code in this workspace.

---

## Project Architecture & Stack

1. **Backend (`backend/`)** — FastAPI, Python 3.11, SQLAlchemy, SQLite, Uvicorn, FAISS, Sentence Transformers, Groq API (LLaMA-3.3-70B), ReportLab.
2. **React Frontend (`react-frontend/`)** — Create React App, React 18, single-file SPA architecture.

> The legacy Streamlit frontend (`frontend/`) is deprecated — do not add features to it.

---

## Critical File Locations

```
backend/main.py                      FastAPI entry — all router registrations
backend/routers/                     auth.py, chat.py, search.py, documents.py, rights.py, news.py
backend/services/llm_service.py      Groq LLaMA-3.3-70B client
backend/services/rag_service.py      FAISS retrieval (threshold: 0.75)
backend/services/doc_service.py      Jinja2 templates + ReportLab PDF generation
backend/db/models.py                 Case, Topic SQLAlchemy models
backend/db/auth_models.py            User model
backend/db/database.py               Engine, SessionLocal, get_db
backend/data/laws/                   Law PDFs for RAG (currently empty)
backend/data/faiss_index/            FAISS output: index.faiss + index.pkl

react-frontend/src/App.jsx           ALL pages, styles, navigation, components (~2100 lines)
react-frontend/src/components/       Layout.jsx
react-frontend/src/pages/            Dashboard.jsx only
react-frontend/package.json          proxy = http://localhost:8000
```

---

## Frontend Architecture

### Single-File Rule
**All pages live in `react-frontend/src/App.jsx`.** This is intentional — do not create new files in `src/pages/` unless the user explicitly asks to split the file.

### Navigation
The app uses **custom `useState`-based SPA routing** — no React Router DOM.
```jsx
// Root App component holds:
const [page, setPage] = useState("home");
const go = (id) => setPage(id);
```
- To add a page: add `{id:"mypage", l:"Label"}` to the `links` array in `Nav`, then handle `page === "mypage"` in the main render block.
- Pass `go` as a prop to pages that need navigation.

### Styling — CSS-in-JS
All styles are defined in `getCSS(theme)` at the top of `App.jsx` and injected into a `<style>` tag at runtime. Design tokens are CSS custom properties:

```css
--gold: #c9a84c     /* buttons, highlights, active borders */
--ink / --ink2      /* body text */
--bg / --bg2        /* page backgrounds */
--surface / --surface2 / --surface3   /* card levels */
--teal: #2a9d8f     /* accents, streaming cursor */
--border / --border2  /* subtle dividers */
```

- Add new styles inside `getCSS(theme)`.
- **Never** create separate `.css` files.
- **Never** use Tailwind utility classes in JSX — the project does not use Tailwind.
- **Never** use `@apply` directives.

### Icons
Use the built-in `<Ico n="..." s={18} c="currentColor"/>` SVG component — do **not** install Lucide React or any icon library.

Available keys: `scale msg srch file shld send user out spk chk arr dn up dl book faq map gavel abc warn copy star note phone close sun moon verify mic micoff tup tdn hist plus trash scan cam cal clk brief tag rf up2 news`

### API Calls
Three wrappers live in `App.jsx` (top of file):
```js
const BASE = "";  // CRA proxy → http://localhost:8000

apiFetch(path)           // GET with auth header
apiPost(path, body)      // POST JSON with auth header
apiBlob(path, body)      // POST, returns Blob (PDF download)
```
- **Never** hardcode `http://localhost:8000` — use `BASE + path` which resolves to `/api/...` via the proxy.
- **Never** call Anthropic, Groq, or any LLM API directly from the browser.

### Auth
- JWT stored in `localStorage` as **`"access_token"`** (not `"token"`).
- Refresh token: `"refresh_token"`.
- All wrappers auto-attach `Authorization: Bearer <access_token>`.
- Logout: `localStorage.clear()`.

### Animations
CSS keyframe animations defined inside `getCSS()`:
- `.fu` — fadeUp (`.6s` fade-in from below)
- `.stream-cursor::after` — blinking cursor for streaming
- `.d1 .d2 .d3` — typing dots
- Custom: `animation:"float 4s ease-in-out infinite"` inline style

Do **not** add Framer Motion — use CSS animations.

### Component Patterns
- Spinner: `<Spin/>` (built-in inline spinner)
- Markdown: `<MarkdownBubble content={text}/>` (uses `marked.parse()`)
- Cards: `className="card"` with optional modifiers `card-gold`, `card-purple`
- Buttons: `className="btn-primary"`, `btn-gold"`, `btn-outline"`, `btn-ghost"`
- Inputs: `className="inp"`
- Badges: `className="badge bt/bg/bb/bp/br/bgr"` (teal/gold/blue/purple/red/green)
- Layout containers: `.wrap` (max 1200px), `.wrap-sm` (max 820px)

---

## Backend Rules

### Setup
```powershell
cd backend
.\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
python -m uvicorn main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
```
IDE "module not found" errors are **false positives** — the venv has the packages, system Python does not. Existing `# pyrefly: ignore` comments handle this.

### Patterns
- Each feature = one router file in `backend/routers/`, registered in `main.py`.
- DB access: `db: Session = Depends(get_db)` in every route — never `SessionLocal()` directly in a route.
- All LLM calls go through `llm_service.py` (`llm_service.chat()` or `llm_service.stream()`).
- All secrets in `backend/.env`. Never hardcode keys.
- SSE streaming: `StreamingResponse` with `media_type="text/event-stream"`.
- Logging: `logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)` per module. No `print()` in routers/services.

### Python Style
- Type hints on all function signatures.
- Pydantic models for all request/response schemas.
- `async def` for route handlers.

### RAG Strictness
- FAISS similarity threshold stays at `0.75` — do not lower without discussion.
- When no context found, return the strict fallback:
  > "I don't have specific information about this in my Pakistan law database. Please consult a qualified Pakistani lawyer for guidance."
- Never hallucinate citations. Always use specific Pakistani Acts (PPC, CrPC, MFLO, CPC, PECA, NAB) with section numbers.
- Never reference Indian laws (IPC) in place of Pakistani law (PPC).

### Document Generation
- Jinja2 templates in `doc_service.py`. Fall back to `.txt` if ReportLab fails.
- All generated PDFs include a legal disclaimer footer.

