## API Endpoints Reference

| Method | Path | Auth | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | /api/auth/register | No | User registration |
| POST | /api/auth/login | No | Login → JWT |
| POST | /api/chat/stream | No | SSE streaming chat |
| POST | /api/search | No | Case law search |
| GET | /api/documents | Yes | List user documents |
| POST | /api/documents/generate | Yes | Generate PDF |
| POST | /api/documents/scan | Yes | Analyze PDF/text |
| GET | /api/rights | No | Legal rights articles |
| GET | /api/news | No | Legal news feed |
| GET | /health | No | Health check |
| GET | /docs | No | FastAPI Swagger UI |

---

## Code Quality Rules

- No comments explaining WHAT code does — only WHY when non-obvious.
- No docstrings longer than one line.
- No error handling for impossible/internal scenarios.
- No abstractions for hypothetical future requirements.
- No half-finished stubs or placeholder implementations.
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones.
- Match the style and patterns in the file being edited.
- No debug `console.log` or `print()` statements in committed code.
- Use `const`/`let` in JS, type hints in Python — never `var`.

---

## Known Gaps (Do Not Work Around Without Discussing)

- `backend/data/laws/` is empty — FAISS RAG is inactive.
- Rate limiter is in-memory only — not Redis-backed.
- JWT in `localStorage` — security debt, acknowledged.
- No unit tests or integration tests.
- Document Scanner image mode unsupported (Groq lacks vision API).

---

## Start Commands

```powershell
# Backend
cd backend && .\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1 && python -m uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000

# Frontend
cd react-frontend && npm start     # http://localhost:3000

# FastAPI docs → http://localhost:8000/docs

# Rebuild FAISS (after adding PDFs to backend/data/laws/)
cd backend && .\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1 && python scripts/ingest_laws.py
```
